after office hours.

139
00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:40,279
Well, I can't spoil him.

140
00:13:41,519 --> 00:13:42,600
He just told me...

141
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:44,120
that a client...

142
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:46,159
terminated the contract.

143
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:51,799
I used to worry...

144
00:13:53,039 --> 00:13:54,480
every day,

145
00:13:55,399 --> 00:13:56,479
but now that...

146
00:13:56,480 --> 00:13:57,639
I overheard your phone conversation.

147
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:04,559
Your phone had a sound leak.

148
00:14:05,679 --> 00:14:06,720
I heard...

149
00:14:07,679 --> 00:14:09,360
a woman's voice...

150
00:14:10,279 --> 00:14:11,279
and she mentioned...

151
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:14,000
Su Su.

152
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:20,519
Is she your ex-girlfriend?

153
00:14:23,039 --> 00:14:24,039
Yes.

154
00:14:34,080 --> 00:14:35,799
It's Su Su's mom.

155
00:14:38,120 --> 00:14:39,199
She doesn't know we broke up.

156
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:40,240
So have you broken up?

157
00:14:55,879 --> 00:14:57,440
- What do you mean?
- What?

158
00:14:58,919 --> 00:15:01,440
Can't you just tell me directly
if you've broken up?

159
00:15:03,720 --> 00:15:05,119
Her mom can call you.

160
00:15:05,120 --> 00:15:06,200
But what about her?

161
00:15:07,440 --> 00:15:09,119
Can she order you around
as she likes,

162
00:15:09,120 --> 00:15:10,120
- Qu Yi Peng?
- Yes.

163
00:15:21,879 --> 00:15:23,320
We're together now.

164
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:25,840
I hope
you won't bring this up again.

165
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:27,360
What do you mean?

166
00:15:27,361 --> 00:15:28,440
What do I mean?

167
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:30,840
He Zhi Nan.

168
00:15:31,919 --> 00:15:32,960
When you came back from the mall,

169
00:15:33,080 --> 00:15:34,879
you said you wouldn't see
your ex-boyfriend anymore,

170
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:36,240
right?

171
00:15:36,559 --> 00:15:37,559
Did you do that?

172
00:15:44,919 --> 00:15:46,320
The two of us are together now,

173
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:49,360
but we both have a past, right?

174
00:15:49,559 --> 00:15:50,879
Our past is not a blank slate.

175
00:15:51,679 --> 00:15:53,240
It was filled with
genuine feelings and efforts.

176
00:15:54,639 --> 00:15:57,440
How can we possibly erase everything
from our past in an instant?

177
00:16:04,240 --> 00:16:05,320
So...

178
00:16:05,919 --> 00:16:07,559
please trust me, okay?

179
00:16:08,240 --> 00:16:09,919
I'll take care of this matter,

180
00:16:10,279 --> 00:16:11,320
but...

181
00:16:11,559 --> 00:16:13,799
But not in the way
and standards you think are right.

182
00:16:15,600 --> 00:16:17,600
I also believe that
you can take care of your matter...

183
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:19,679
in your own way and standards.

184
00:16:38,840 --> 00:16:39,840
Let's not talk...

185
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:42,279
about them anymore, okay?

186
00:17:02,759 --> 00:17:03,799
Nan Nan.

187
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:09,410
We are human after all.

188
00:17:10,279 --> 00:17:11,440
We have feelings.

189
00:17:13,279 --> 00:17:14,920
If you value the future,

190
00:17:16,599 --> 00:17:17,759
you'll surely honour the past.

191
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:19,039
Right?

192
00:17:23,359 --> 00:17:24,799
When I'm with you,

193
00:17:25,359 --> 00:17:26,759
I feel calm...

194
00:17:28,319 --> 00:17:29,480
and relaxed.

195
00:17:31,319 --> 00:17:32,960
That's why I don't want us...

196
00:17:34,039 --> 00:17:35,960
to get caught up
in meaningless arguments,

197
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:38,000
doubts,

198
00:17:38,599 --> 00:17:39,650
and defensiveness.

199
00:17:40,720 --> 00:17:41,759
Otherwise, in the end,

200
00:17:43,039 --> 00:17:44,319
we'll both be exhausted...

201
00:17:45,240 --> 00:17:46,440
and our hearts will grow cold
from all the fighting.

202
00:18:02,279 --> 00:18:03,319
I'm sorry.

203
00:18:06,759 --> 00:18:07,799
I'm sorry.

204
00:18:08,359 --> 00:18:09,440
Don't be angry, okay?

205
00:18:11,359 --> 00:18:12,359
Let me hug you.

206
00:18:20,039 --> 00:18:21,039
I'm sorry.

207
00:18:22,599 --> 00:18:23,599
I like you.

208
00:18:23,960 --> 00:18:25,000
I'm serious.

209
00:20:25,559 --> 00:20:26,599
Hello, Su Su.

210
00:20:26,890 --> 00:20:29,000
I worked overtime last night.

211
00:20:29,240 --> 00:20:31,240
I called you when I got home,
but your phone was off.

212
00:20:35,279 --> 00:20:36,279
What's the matter?

213
00:20:36,359 --> 00:20:37,440
Are you angry with me?

214
00:20:43,960 --> 00:20:45,039
Qu Yi Peng.

215
00:20:48,720 --> 00:20:49,799
Let's break up.

216
00:21:23,720 --> 00:21:24,759
Okay.

217
00:21:27,680 --> 00:21:29,890
So you neither want
to hear the reasons...

218
00:21:30,519 --> 00:21:31,890
nor try to hold on, right?

219
00:21:32,170 --> 00:21:33,200
There's nothing worth holding on to.

220
00:21:35,519 --> 00:21:36,599
You...

221
00:21:37,410 --> 00:21:38,440
don't like me anyway.

222
00:21:45,680 --> 00:21:46,720
Han Su.

223
00:21:48,799 --> 00:21:49,890
I know you too well.

224
00:21:51,400 --> 00:21:52,559
I know...

225
00:21:54,599 --> 00:21:55,839
you're ambitious.

226
00:22:00,440 --> 00:22:02,000
You want to climb up the ladder.

227
00:22:04,359 --> 00:22:06,480
I can't keep up with you.

228
00:22:07,640 --> 00:22:08,640
I'm...

229
00:22:09,160 --> 00:22:10,200
not good enough...

230
00:22:12,440 --> 00:22:13,799
for you.

231
00:22:16,279 --> 00:22:18,359
By going to Hong Kong,
aren‘t you making it clear...

232
00:22:19,200 --> 00:22:20,279
that you want to break up with me?

233
00:22:25,400 --> 00:22:26,480
Hello?

234
00:22:28,640 --> 00:22:29,720
I can hear you.

235
00:22:34,599 --> 00:22:35,880
Actually,

236
00:22:38,799 --> 00:22:40,079
